  "body": "### Describe the bug\n\nAs found in https://github.com/ChainSafe/lodestar/issues/5650#issuecomment-1592822730, when node is syncing it may also receive unknown block root event (especially in a setup with fallback urls), there is no need to search for block at that time\r\n\r\nalso this is to avoid this case https://github.com/ChainSafe/lodestar/blob/2eddf466394680cb1c6a24700b9a3a2958a3ef90/packages/beacon-node/src/sync/unknownBlock.ts#L228\r\n\r\n\n\n### Expected behavior\n\nOnly start/init unknown block sync once the node is synced\n\n### Steps to reproduce\n\n_No response_\n\n### Additional context\n\n_No response_\n\n### Operating system\n\nLinux\n\n### Lodestar version or commit hash\n\nv1.9.0-rc.2",
